497
00:39:05,720 --> 00:39:07,600
I don't think there's anything 
controversial about that. If  

498
00:39:07,600 --> 00:39:10,920
you're a cool company that everyone 
wants to work at, people will pay,  

499
00:39:10,920 --> 00:39:15,066
will take less salary because of the experience 
they're going to get and the potential.

500
00:39:15,066 --> 00:39:19,760
That's right. And the other problem I 
realized is that when you overpay people,  

501
00:39:19,760 --> 00:39:23,800
what happens is that they actually become 
more and more scared that they will lose it,  

502
00:39:23,800 --> 00:39:27,000
and then they become more and more conservative 
because they don't want to rock the boat and they  

503
00:39:27,000 --> 00:39:31,720
actually don't work. They do what they're told 
as opposed to do what they should do. And so you  

504
00:39:31,720 --> 00:39:38,080
